<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>1987-11-30</DATELINE><TITLE>Les gastroenterites virales</TITLE><BODY>Summary Many virus are able to induce gastroenteritis, especially in young children with immunological or nutritional defects. The most frequently observed, using ELISA, are Rotavirus. The others : Norwalk agent, Coronavirus, Breda virus, are identified using electron microscope. Using symptomatic therapy, prognosis is related to precocious hydratation.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>